121
00:05:45,110 --> 00:05:46,150
We were lost.

122
00:05:46,150 --> 00:05:46,930
We weren't lost.

123
00:05:46,930 --> 00:05:49,740
Our vehicle ran out of gas 20 miles from here.

124
00:05:49,740 --> 00:05:52,740
We took a shortcut through the woods so we could avoid the Zs.

125
00:05:52,740 --> 00:05:54,100
You're not lost anymore.

126
00:05:54,560 --> 00:05:56,600
Welcome to Edgemont, South Dakota.

127
00:05:56,890 --> 00:06:00,450
Population three, not counting you.

128
00:06:00,680 --> 00:06:02,280
Name's Wilbur Grady.

129
00:06:02,310 --> 00:06:04,240
This is my daughter, Amelia.

130
00:06:04,240 --> 00:06:05,100
Nice to meet you.

131
00:06:05,100 --> 00:06:06,750
Nice meeting you. I'm Roberta Warren.

132
00:06:06,750 --> 00:06:07,660
This is Murphy.

133
00:06:07,660 --> 00:06:10,530
And that's Cassandra. And this is 10K in the back.

134
00:06:17,420 --> 00:06:18,580
Is he okay?

135
00:06:18,740 --> 00:06:20,990
No. Radiation poisoning.

136
00:06:21,130 --> 00:06:22,270
I'm fine.

137
00:06:22,830 --> 00:06:23,910
Let's get you folks checked out

138
00:06:23,910 --> 00:06:25,230
and get you some food.

139
00:06:25,620 --> 00:06:28,390
Our place is just around here down the road a little ways.

140
00:06:39,140 --> 00:06:40,100
What are these?

141
00:06:40,150 --> 00:06:41,150
Iodine.

142
00:06:43,000 --> 00:06:46,210
It'll keep the radiation from accumulating in your thyroid.

143
00:06:46,350 --> 00:06:47,410
Yeah, right.

144
00:06:48,460 --> 00:06:50,640
Looks like you're still within safe levels.

145
00:06:51,040 --> 00:06:53,030
But you're lucky we came along when we did.

146
00:06:53,150 --> 00:06:55,920
Most of the Zs around here are highly radioactive.

147
00:06:55,920 --> 00:06:59,130
As if being brain-eating zombies wasn't bad enough.

148
00:06:59,130 --> 00:07:00,440
Okay. Question.

149
00:07:00,670 --> 00:07:02,870
Shouldn't we be in one of these suits too?

150
00:07:02,870 --> 00:07:05,170
Radiation levels aren't too bad out here.

151
00:07:06,150 --> 00:07:09,070
But you'll probably get cancer in twenty years.

152
00:07:09,140 --> 00:07:11,360
Somehow that's way down on my list of worries.

153
00:07:11,360 --> 00:07:13,250
Yeah, but our more immediate problem

154
00:07:13,250 --> 00:07:15,050
is the reactor core melting down.

155
00:07:15,170 --> 00:07:16,250
We don't fix it soon,

156
00:07:16,250 --> 00:07:19,150
then everything within a 300 mile radius will be glowing.

157
00:07:19,390 --> 00:07:20,250
Not just the Zs.

158
00:07:20,250 --> 00:07:22,060
Okay, well

159
00:07:22,380 --> 00:07:23,710
it's been nice meeting you.

160
00:07:23,820 --> 00:07:25,380
We have places to be,

161
00:07:25,380 --> 00:07:27,190
places at least 300 miles from here.

162
00:07:27,190 --> 00:07:28,370
Good luck with that.

163
00:07:28,670 --> 00:07:30,890
Every vehicle in town is gone

164
00:07:30,890 --> 00:07:32,910
or can't be driven.

165
00:07:33,510 --> 00:07:35,000
Then I guess we better start walking.

166
00:07:35,000 --> 00:07:36,170
You won't make it.

167
00:07:36,560 --> 00:07:39,510
We have less than 48 hours before the core starts to melt down.

168
00:07:39,510 --> 00:07:40,900
Why are you still here?

169
00:07:40,930 --> 00:07:42,630
Because there's still a chance to shut this thing down

170
00:07:42,630 --> 00:07:44,350
and save a big chunk of God's country

171
00:07:44,350 --> 00:07:47,250
from being irradiated for the next 10,000 years.

172
00:07:47,540 --> 00:07:50,690
Besides I'm already a goner.

173
00:07:51,610 --> 00:07:52,900
Well what about your daughter?

174
00:07:52,900 --> 00:07:55,090
Did she sign up for this suicide mission too?

175
00:07:55,090 --> 00:07:56,690
I am sticking around to help my dad.

176
00:07:56,690 --> 00:07:59,360
I told her I didn't need her help,

177
00:08:00,140 --> 00:08:01,890
but she wouldn't listen.

178
00:08:01,890 --> 00:08:02,970
I'm a pilot.

179
00:08:02,970 --> 00:08:04,360
I'll fly us out of the hot zone.

180
00:08:04,360 --> 00:08:05,660
Well perfect.

181
00:08:05,660 --> 00:08:06,960
We'll just hitch a ride.

182
00:08:06,960 --> 00:08:07,650
Yeah.

183
00:08:07,650 --> 00:08:10,910
As you can see there's only room for one passenger.

184
00:08:11,030 --> 00:08:12,380
And I have enough bullets for all of you,

185
00:08:12,380 --> 00:08:14,520
so don't go getting any ideas.

186
00:08:14,800 --> 00:08:17,040
Mister Grady, Wilbur.

187
00:08:17,740 --> 00:08:18,690
I know it doesn't look like it,

188
00:08:18,690 --> 00:08:20,360
but this man...

189
00:08:20,460 --> 00:08:24,050
this man is the only known survivor of a zombie bite.

190
00:08:25,200 --> 00:08:26,980
Thought there was something wrong with him.

191
00:08:27,420 --> 00:08:30,810
His blood carries antibodies for the zombie virus.

192
00:08:31,760 --> 00:08:34,070
He's our last best hope for humanity.

193
00:08:38,690 --> 00:08:41,940
Yeah right, and I'm the Easter bunny.

194
00:08:42,930 --> 00:08:43,920
Show him.

195
00:08:48,830 --> 00:08:49,970
Oh my God.

196
00:08:51,380 --> 00:08:52,340
Now look, man.

197
00:08:52,340 --> 00:08:53,840
This dude here's the real deal.

198
00:08:54,310 --> 00:08:56,700
And a lot of people got killed getting him this far.

199
00:08:57,200 --> 00:08:59,610
So tell us what we need to do to shut down that reactor

200
00:08:59,610 --> 00:09:01,400
so we can be on our way.

201
00:09:01,400 --> 00:09:05,710
