not nukes.

294
00:14:22,740 --> 00:14:23,860
Awesome.

295
00:14:24,920 --> 00:14:26,700
I mean there's one guy.

296
00:14:27,310 --> 00:14:29,180
Here, here in Edgemont?

297
00:14:29,430 --> 00:14:31,610
Yeah, Homer Stubbins.

298
00:14:31,720 --> 00:14:36,450
He was the chief engineer at the plant for 20 years.

299
00:14:36,610 --> 00:14:38,060
He was dad's boss.

300
00:14:39,800 --> 00:14:42,280
He's been holed up in the woods since the apocalypse.

301
00:14:42,310 --> 00:14:44,400
He's armed and dangerous.

302
00:14:44,510 --> 00:14:46,960
He became a recluse after the death of his son.

303
00:14:47,920 --> 00:14:49,700
How do we find Homer?

304
00:14:50,520 --> 00:14:52,240
He won't talk to you.

305
00:14:53,430 --> 00:14:54,770
We have to try.

306
00:15:08,290 --> 00:15:09,480
We have to stop here.

307
00:15:10,090 --> 00:15:11,800
We're still fifty yards away.

308
00:15:11,800 --> 00:15:13,650
My dad said the place was booby-trapped.

309
00:15:13,650 --> 00:15:15,270
I told you, Homer's crazy.

310
00:15:15,470 --> 00:15:17,900
Have we completely dismissed the idea of a phone call?

311
00:15:18,030 --> 00:15:19,220
Just sayin'.

312
00:15:22,740 --> 00:15:24,200
This is your kinda set-up. 

313
00:15:24,210 --> 00:15:25,430
How do we get in?

314
00:15:25,430 --> 00:15:27,090
Without us getting killed. 

315
00:15:27,090 --> 00:15:29,000
I do like to keep that in mind.

316
00:15:29,410 --> 00:15:30,430
Uh, well one thing.

317
00:15:30,430 --> 00:15:33,050
Homer's set-up is aimed at stopping Zs, not a team. 

318
00:15:33,060 --> 00:15:37,170
So if we keep a sharp eye out for landmines, trip wires...

319
00:15:37,170 --> 00:15:38,330
We'll be fine.

320
00:15:40,700 --> 00:15:41,720
Okay.

321
00:15:43,420 --> 00:15:45,170
The three of you guys, stay here.

322
00:15:45,400 --> 00:15:46,740
Give us a 40 second head start.

323
00:15:46,750 --> 00:15:49,260
We'll flank him and come up from behind.

324
00:16:09,340 --> 00:16:10,750
Okay, watch for mines.

325
00:16:10,750 --> 00:16:11,940
Watching them.

326
00:16:35,440 --> 00:16:36,530
Don't move!

327
00:16:37,050 --> 00:16:39,340
You have three seconds to tell me what you're doing here.

328
00:16:39,340 --> 00:16:40,370
One.

329
00:16:40,670 --> 00:16:41,710
Two.

330
00:16:42,450 --> 00:16:43,710
Don't do that, sir.

331
00:16:44,150 --> 00:16:46,880
Go ahead. Do me a solid.

332
00:16:46,940 --> 00:16:48,640
Just don't leave me a Z.

333
00:16:49,300 --> 00:16:51,070
I'd never do that, Mr. Stubbins.

334
00:16:51,070 --> 00:16:52,580
We just need your help.

335
00:16:53,000 --> 00:16:54,560
Hello to you too.

336
00:17:01,670 --> 00:17:03,120
Grady was a good man.

337
00:17:04,090 --> 00:17:07,490
If anyone could SCRAM that reactor

338
00:17:08,040 --> 00:17:09,210
it was him.

339
00:17:10,240 --> 00:17:11,370
Scram?

340
00:17:11,460 --> 00:17:14,580
Safety Control Rod Axe Man.

341
00:17:14,910 --> 00:17:17,100
Goes back to the first reactors.

342
00:17:17,100 --> 00:17:20,610
The only safety system they had was literally 

343
00:17:20,680 --> 00:17:22,120
a man with an axe

344
00:17:22,120 --> 00:17:25,100
whose whole job in the event of a meltdown

345
00:17:25,360 --> 00:17:29,390
was to cut the rope holding fuel rods over the cooling pool.

346
00:17:29,390 --> 00:17:31,350
That's what dad was trying to do.

347
00:17:31,550 --> 00:17:33,040
How much time do you have?

348
00:17:33,040 --> 00:17:34,150
How much time do we have?

349
00:17:34,150 --> 00:17:35,730
You're in the soup with us, Homer.

350
00:17:35,730 --> 00:17:38,260
You've confused me with someone who gives a damn.

351
00:17:38,260 --> 00:17:41,170
According to Grady, less than 40 hours.

352
00:17:41,170 --> 00:17:42,960
And we do give a damn.

353
00:17:42,990 --> 00:17:44,060
Now are you gonna help us

354
00:17:44,060 --> 00:17:46,710
or are you gonna sit here and let us all die?

355
00:17:49,230 --> 00:17:51,490
Well there's one thing we might try.

356
00:17:53,210 --> 00:17:54,770
I'm gonna have to show you.

357
00:17:58,310 --> 00:18:01,540
We're gonna need weapons, equipment.

358
00:18:02,800 --> 00:18:04,780
Come on. Load up.

359
00:18:04,990 --> 00:18:07,840
It's not as if I'm gonna be needing this stuff.

360
00:18:11,970 --> 00:18:13,490
Hello, nurse.

361
00:18:15,290 --> 00:18:19,580
Vitamin V. The elixir of the Zombie Apocalypse.

362
00:18:28,920 --> 00:18:31,130
You know you're looking at the original building plans

363
00:18:31,130 --> 00:18:32,540
for this reactor.

364
00:18:32,870 --> 00:18:35,160
I was part of the design team.

365
00:18:36,760 --> 00:18:39,450
You're pretty handy with that knife

366
00:18:39,450 --> 00:18:40,640
for a kid.

367
00:18:41,700 --> 00:18:42,890
My son...

368
00:18:44,570 --> 00:18:45,890
he had one like it

369
00:18:46,600 --> 00:18:48,690
but with a longer blade.

370
00:18:48,760 --> 00:18:50,090
Yeah, older model.

371
00:18:50,580 --> 00:18:52,290
Got to be good to make it work.

372
00:18:52,290 --> 00:18:53,900
Oh, Max was good.

373
00:18:55,580 --> 00:18:57,340
Okay, let's go, let's do it.

374
00:18:57,410 --> 00:18:58,780
I heard about your son.

375
00:19:00,310 --> 00:19:01,380
I'm sorry.

376
00:19:02,820 --> 00:19:06,250
There's nothing worse than outliving your own child.

377
00:19:06,250 --> 00:19:07,330
Nothing.

378
00:19:10,930 --> 00:19:13,860
There sure is a whole lot of nothing in South Dakota, huh boy?

379
00:19:18,320 --> 00:19:19,370
Dammit.

381
00:19:21,950 --> 00:19:23,120
What the hell?

382
00:19:23,540 --> 00:19:24,930
A satellite phone?

383
00:19:25,530 --> 00:19:26,710
Is it my team?

384
00:19:27,630 --> 00:19:28,900
Oh, rats.

386
00:19:30,230 --> 00:19:31,830
Northern Light, come in.

387
00:19:32,480 --> 00:19:34,970
I don't know what you want with that old piece of junk.

388
00:19:35,040 --> 00:19:36,250
Nobody to call.

389
00:19:36,250 --> 00:19:38,080
We got somebody that might pick up.

390
00:19:39,580 --> 00:19:40,980
Northern Light, come in.

391
00:19:43,720 --> 00:19:45,000
Something wrong, Homer?

392
00:19:47,640 --> 00:19:49,410
I knew her, that's all.

393
00:19:50,090 --> 00:19:52,420
Her son was one of Max's buddies.

394
00:19:55,400 --> 00:19:57,850
Did you ever go back to the house you grew up in

395
00:19:57,850 --> 00:20:01,500
only to see it's falling apart and in a bad neighborhood?

396
00:20:01,530 --> 00:20:03,480
That's what this feels like.

397
00:20:03,640 --> 00:20:04,920
Times ten.

398
00:20:05,280 --> 00:20:08,900
Well where I grew up, the Zombie Apocalypse only improved things.

399
00:20:17,580 --> 00:20:19,120
All right, back to business.

400
00:20:19,280 --> 00:20:21,610
From here on the area's hot, right?

401
00:20:21,860 --> 00:20:24,410
You got two clean rad suits in there.

402
00:20:24,430 --> 00:20:25,990
One for me and

403
00:20:26,900 --> 00:20:28,930
I need somebody to back me up.

404
00:20:29,770 --> 00:20:30,650
No. I'll go.

405
00:20:30,650 --> 00:20:32,050
Well you can't go.

406
00:20:33,880 --> 00:20:35,240
Who's gonna get him to California

407
00:20:35,240 --> 00:20:36,430
if something goes wrong?

408
00:20:36,820 --> 00:20:37,980
Don't look at me.

409
00:20:39,460 --> 00:20:41,700
Okay. All right.

410
00:20:41,780 --> 00:20:44,110
Just remember you have ammo now.

411
00:20:44,250 --> 00:20:46,280
But not an infinite supply.

412
00:20:46,730 --> 00:20:47,910
Let's do this.

414
00:21:04,320 --> 00:21:06,230
We made it to the control room.

415
00:21:10,870 --> 00:21:12,470
And there's our problem.

416
00:21:12,500 --> 00:21:14,180
Cooling pool three.

417
00:21:14,180 --> 00:21:15,520
Can you SCRAM it or not?

418
00:21:15,880 --> 00:21:19,080
According to the controls, all the rods are enabled

419
00:21:19,080 --> 00:21:22,440
but something is physically blocking the insertion.

420
00:21:22,950 --> 00:21:24,140
We need to remove it.

421
00:21:24,140 --> 00:21:25,270
By hand?

422
00:21:27,970 --> 00:21:29,750
Not by our hand.

423
00:21:35,860 --> 00:21:37,180
This is Robbie.

424
00:21:37,240 --> 00:21:40,490
He will roll into the core and do a manual SCRAM.

425
00:21:40,500 --> 00:21:42,700
He can cut through anything.

426
00:21:42,900 --> 00:21:46,290
This little darlin' can vaporize steel.

427
00:21:49,650 --> 00:21:50,760
I get it.

428
00:21:51,080 --> 00:21:52,240
It's like a drone.

429
00:21:52,250 --> 00:21:54,830
Only he never leaves the ground.

430
00:22:08,660 --> 00:22:10,130
There's too many Zs.

431
00:22:10,380 --> 00:22:11,330
Back it up, Homer.

432
00:22:11,330 --> 00:22:12,690
I'll do the driving.

433
00:22:12,690 --> 00:22:14,230
We need to go forward.

434
00:22:22,490 --> 00:22:24,180
Damn Zs got us.

435
00:22:25,120 --> 00:22:26,900
You're an ugly one.

436
00:22:35,580 --> 00:22:36,840
Damn Z.

437
00:22:37,350 --> 00:22:39,490
I don't have time for this.

438
00:22:48,710 --> 00:22:49,660
Get 'em out of there.

439
00:22:49,660 --> 00:22:51,790
Damn Z. Leave.

440
00:23:00,800 --> 00:23:02,490
We lost Robbie.

441
00:23:06,440 --> 00:23:07,620
So what now?

442
00:23:08,040 --> 00:23:10,220
Plan B or is it C?

443
00:23:10,220 --> 00:23:12,730
Give me a D, E, F.

444
00:23:12,730 --> 00:23:14,210
Not helpful.

445
00:23:15,560 --> 00:23:17,680
All right. Robbie failed.

446
00:23:18,350 --> 00:23:20,690
But I can still do a manual SCRAM.

447
00:23:20,700 --> 00:23:23,170
How? That place is filled with Zs.

448
00:23:23,170 --> 00:23:24,800
We'll go in heavier.

449
00:23:24,800 --> 00:23:26,490
Take us along this time.

450
00:23:26,490 --> 00:23:29,480
We probably only got one more shot at a SCRAM.

451
00:23:30,520 --> 00:23:32,990
But we'll need heavier suits to reach the control room.

452
00:23:32,990 --> 00:23:34,220
Where do we find them?

453
00:23:35,320 --> 00:23:38,540
In the lab, not far from where we lost Robbie.

454
00:23:38,840 --> 00:23:41,280
Four can go in, two in these suits.

455
00:23:41,280 --> 00:23:42,870
Me and the kid in the heavies.

456
00:23:42,870 --> 00:23:43,810
Okay.

457
00:23:43,820 --> 00:23:46,120
But what happens if plan C doesn't work

458
00:23:46,120 --> 00:23:50,370
and we wind up with our very own Fukushima Chernobyl whatever?

459
00:23:50,380 --> 00:23:52,000
You mean what happens to you?

460
00:23:52,520 --> 00:23:55,470
I didn't ask for the job of saving the human race.

461
00:23:56,190 --> 00:23:57,220
Amelia.

462
00:23:57,250 --> 00:23:59,990
Would you be willing to fly him out of the radiation zone?

463
00:24:01,830 --> 00:24:03,050
To be honest,

464
00:24:03,340 --> 00:24:04,710
I don't have enough fuel.

465
00:24:04,760 --> 00:24:05,700
I lied to my dad or else

466
00:24:05,700 --> 00:24:07,250
he never would have let me stay behind.

467
00:24:07,250 --> 00:24:08,570
Great.

468
00:24:09,060 --> 00:24:10,650
If I had a few gallons,

469
00:24:10,650 --> 00:24:12,560
I might be able to get myself and one other person

470
00:24:12,560 --> 00:24:15,410
outside the blast zone, if we are lucky.

471
00:24:17,270 --> 00:24:20,600
Okay, a buddy and I once converted a Dodge Dart

472
00:24:20,600 --> 00:24:22,480
to run on alcohol.

473
00:24:22,480 --> 00:24:24,840
A light plane engine isn't that different.

474
00:24:24,840 --> 00:24:26,910
You had a serious supply of vodka.

475
00:24:26,950 --> 00:24:28,550
You're welcome to it.

476
00:24:29,020 --> 00:24:30,040
Okay.

477
00:24:30,680 --> 00:24:32,030
Doc and Cassandra,

478
00:24:32,030 --> 00:24:34,550
go with 10K and Homer. You cover them.

479
00:24:34,560 --> 00:24:36,500
Murphy and Amelia, come with me.

480
00:24:36,780 --> 00:24:38,590
Given we have no other choices,

481
00:24:38,590 --> 00:24:40,740
I shall embrace the inevitable.

482
00:24:40,790 --> 00:24:43,630
If this works, we'll meet back here to celebrate.

484
00:24:54,110 --> 00:24:59,080
That's not good. We have 30 minutes till boom.

485
00:24:59,660 --> 00:25:01,080
Brave little dude.

486
00:25:01,470 --> 00:25:03,290
Too bad we have to leave him here like this.

487
00:25:03,300 --> 00:25:04,910
Sentiment is a fatal flaw

488
00:25:04,910 --> 00:25:07,250
in this ugly world.

489
00:25:08,510 --> 00:25:09,710
We should let Warren know where we are 

490
00:25:09,710 --> 00:25:11,410
in case we need backup, right?

491
00:25:12,620 --> 00:25:14,610
Warren, this is Doc.

492
00:25:14,610 --> 00:25:16,330
Please be advised we have entered the tunnel

493
00:25:16,330 --> 00:25:17,700
to the reactor core. 

494
00:25:17,700 --> 00:25:18,960
Over and out.

495
00:25:19,450 --> 00:25:21,300
Let's see what's going on with this baby.

496
00:25:22,630 --> 00:25:24,550
So Amelia, my dear.

497
00:25:25,510 --> 00:25:27,130
Where exactly might we be headed

498
00:25:27,130 --> 00:25:29,760
in this fine piece of aeronautical hardware?

499
00:25:29,760 --> 00:25:31,690
Considering it's only my life 

500
00:25:31,690 --> 00:25:33,580
and the human race at stake.

501
00:25:33,580 --> 00:25:34,810
Sheridan, Wyoming.

502
00:25:34,810 --> 00:25:35,650
It's to the northwest,

503
00:25:35,650 --> 00:25:37,960
and the fallout will be to the southeast.

504
00:25:37,960 --> 00:25:39,420
Far enough away, and

505
00:25:39,570 --> 00:25:42,220
my dad and I heard there's some real humans.

506
00:25:43,060 --> 00:25:44,440
I just hope it works.

507
00:25:44,620 --> 00:25:46,860
Piece of cake. All I need is some tools.

508
00:25:50,810 --> 00:25:53,430
Murphy, could you quit drinking your fuel

509
00:25:53,440 --> 00:25:55,320
and fill up the damn tank?

510
00:25:55,530 --> 00:25:57,450
I don't know where the tank is.

511
00:25:57,590 --> 00:25:59,380
Well it's not in your mouth.

512
00:25:59,560 --> 00:26:00,980
Let me get a screwdriver.

513
00:26:10,910 --> 00:26:13,780
Okay, so that was 22 gallons.

514
00:26:13,780 --> 00:26:16,680
Sheridan is 250 miles as the crow flies.

515
00:26:16,680 --> 00:26:17,990
Here's a couple more.

516
00:26:18,880 --> 00:26:21,180
Is that gonna be far enough to clear the blast zone?

517
00:26:21,180 --> 00:26:22,380
It'll have to be.

518
00:26:22,460 --> 00:26:24,070
Well this is vodka, not avgas. 

519
00:26:24,070 --> 00:26:25,910
So the mileage may vary.

520
00:26:34,460 --> 00:26:35,540
Listen, I, uhhh...

521
00:26:35,550 --> 00:26:39,890
Oh shit, you're not gonna try and say goodbye, are you?

522
00:26:44,520 --> 00:26:46,380
I was going to say

523
00:26:47,100 --> 00:26:50,980
be grateful for all the sacrifices everyone has made.

524
00:27:14,110 --> 00:27:15,290
Back at you.

525
00:28:04,050 --> 00:28:05,310
Are we there yet?

526
00:28:05,900 --> 00:28:08,010
We've been in the air for five minutes.

527
00:28:10,450 --> 00:28:14,130
You know, I kinda like this. You can't see any zombies.

528
00:28:14,170 --> 00:28:16,470
They're down there, bet on it.

529
00:28:16,490 --> 00:28:19,350
Hey, if we find more fuel in Billings,

530
00:28:19,350 --> 00:28:21,950
we could take off again and head to California.

531
00:28:22,430 --> 00:28:23,950
If we find vodka.

532
00:28:24,280 --> 00:28:27,400
I don't know how to change this carburetor back to a gas-burner.

533
00:28:30,990 --> 00:28:32,680
Doc, this is Warren, back at the plant,

534
00:28:32,690 --> 00:28:34,160
coming in the same way.

535
00:28:38,120 --> 00:28:39,490
Doc, Warren.

536
00:28:39,860 --> 00:28:41,930
Hello, Roberta. Welcome back.

537
00:28:41,930 --> 00:28:44,390
Please be advised we're now entering the reactor core

538
00:28:44,400 --> 00:28:46,160
on the other side of the facility.

539
00:28:46,390 --> 00:28:47,660
Is there something I can do?

540
00:28:47,660 --> 00:28:49,720
Oh, just the usual prayer.

541
00:28:49,970 --> 00:28:52,650
What's the status of that precious cargo?

542
00:28:52,660 --> 00:28:54,920
Has the mouthy package taken off?

543
00:28:55,280 --> 00:28:56,590
Yeah, he's in the air.

544
00:29:00,220 --> 00:29:02,110
Then we'll fix our little problem.

545
00:29:04,000 --> 00:29:05,620
And see you on the way out.

546
00:29:09,810 --> 00:29:11,200
Will you miss your friends?

547
00:29:12,200 --> 00:29:13,520
They're not my friends.

548
00:29:14,870 --> 00:29:16,990
More like foxhole buddies.

549
00:29:19,190 --> 00:29:20,230
But yeah.

550
00:29:22,030 --> 00:29:23,670
- What's going on? Wait. - I...

551
00:29:23,670 --> 00:29:24,980
- What is that? - I got it.

552
00:29:26,540 --> 00:29:28,040
Just a little turbulence.

553
00:29:36,020 --> 00:29:36,890
Oh God!

554
00:29:37,330 --> 00:29:38,200
Hang on.

555
00:29:38,360 --> 00:29:39,750
- Shut up and hang on! - Oh God!

556
00:29:39,750 --> 00:29:40,800
Oh God!

557
00:30:10,030 --> 00:30:10,970
Amelia!

558
00:30:15,380 --> 00:30:16,700
Oh God, no.

559
00:30:37,980 --> 00:30:38,850
Mercy.

560
00:30:39,260 --> 00:30:40,080
Mercy.

561
00:30:40,440 --> 00:30:41,210
Mercy.

562
00:31:08,390 --> 00:31:09,460
It's weird.

563
00:31:10,400 --> 00:31:11,460
It's too weird.

564
00:31:39,090 --> 00:31:39,610
All right.

565
00:31:39,610 --> 00:31:43,180
Which one of you fine vehicles is our ride out of here?

566
00:31:55,280 --> 00:31:56,520
Hello, Delta-X-Ray.

567
00:31:56,520 --> 00:31:58,120
This is Delta-X-Ray, copy.

568
00:31:58,120 --> 00:32:01,160
I need a little information on glowing zombies.

569
00:32:02,800 --> 00:32:04,970
Okay. Checking zombie-pedia.

570
00:32:04,970 --> 00:32:06,190
Are you kidding?

571
00:32:06,450 --> 00:32:08,240
For now, but it's not a bad idea.

572
00:32:08,660 --> 00:32:10,570
Okay. It's called 'Angel's Glow.'

573
00:32:10,570 --> 00:32:12,770
Comes from nematode bacteria.

574
00:32:12,770 --> 00:32:14,840
Somehow the radiation affects zombie skin

575
00:32:14,840 --> 00:32:16,350
and lets bacteria grow there.

576
00:32:16,350 --> 00:32:19,380
The bacteria glows when exposed to high levels of radiation.

577
00:32:19,380 --> 00:32:20,980
First observed at Fukushima.

578
00:32:20,980 --> 00:32:22,690
I just need an answer. Are they hot or not?

579
00:32:22,690 --> 00:32:23,840
Don't let them

580
00:32:24,510 --> 00:32:25,670
spatter you.

581
00:32:27,600 --> 00:32:28,490
Shoot.

582
00:32:36,290 --> 00:32:37,300
Still there?

583
00:32:39,780 --> 00:32:40,640
Yeah.

584
00:32:41,200 --> 00:32:42,780
I got no other place to be.

585
00:32:51,160 --> 00:32:52,320
How you feeling?

586
00:32:52,730 --> 00:32:54,690
Like a baked potato in this thing.

587
00:32:55,990 --> 00:32:58,160
Reactor core is right down this corridor.

588
00:32:58,160 --> 00:32:59,910
Then why are we standing here?

589
00:32:59,920 --> 00:33:02,550
Because it's highly radioactive in there.

590
00:33:03,260 --> 00:33:06,190
I'm going into the core to manually insert those rods.

591
00:33:06,200 --> 00:33:07,340
By yourself?

592
00:33:09,310 --> 00:33:10,400
Out of my way, sonny.

593
00:33:10,400 --> 00:33:12,000
I'm sorry. You need backup.

594
00:33:15,010 --> 00:33:16,210
Suit yourself.

595
00:33:16,690 --> 00:33:18,030
You guys go. I've got it.

596
00:33:18,030 --> 00:33:18,990
Take this.

597
00:33:19,450 --> 00:33:21,270
And we need to hear everything!

598
00:33:21,560 --> 00:33:23,020
All right! Go on! Move it!

599
00:33:24,920 --> 00:33:25,860
Come on!

600
00:33:59,120 --> 00:34:01,710
That guy came out of nowhere. I couldn't move fast enough.

601
00:34:03,120 --> 00:34:07,540
It's one of those good news, really really bad news things.

602
00:34:07,540 --> 00:34:09,150
The suit is breached.

603
00:34:09,150 --> 00:34:10,570
Can I tape it up?

604
00:34:11,330 --> 00:34:14,470
Son, I've accumulated so many rads in my life,

605
00:34:14,470 --> 00:34:15,920
I was probably a dead man

606
00:34:15,930 --> 00:34:17,800
the moment I walked through the gate.

607
00:34:18,560 --> 00:34:20,330
There's got to be something I can do.

608
00:34:23,560 --> 00:34:25,390
Aren't you gonna add to your count?

609
00:34:27,390 --> 00:34:29,810
Two thousand three hundred and sixteen.

610
00:34:31,110 --> 00:34:33,940
You know you're a good kid, 

611
00:34:34,160 --> 00:34:37,990
strong, smart, like my son Max.

612
00:34:38,930 --> 00:34:41,410
I just hope to God you have better luck.

613
00:34:41,990 --> 00:34:43,780
You're a lot like my dad too.

614
00:34:45,880 --> 00:34:48,410
With the same bad luck.

615
00:34:49,790 --> 00:34:52,840
You need to go on for all of us.

616
00:34:52,990 --> 00:34:54,360
Promise me that.

617
00:34:55,030 --> 00:34:59,170
Live the life...my son never had.

618
00:35:03,460 --> 00:35:04,790
We need to get up there.

619
00:35:16,470 --> 00:35:18,460
Time really is a waistin'.

620
00:35:18,830 --> 00:35:20,350
Let's get to it.

621
00:35:21,910 --> 00:35:23,430
There's our problem.

622
00:35:23,430 --> 00:35:25,510
Two rods didn't go down.

623
00:35:25,600 --> 00:35:29,460
I'm gonna have to go out there and unstick those rods.

624
00:35:29,590 --> 00:35:32,360
Be careful not to drop me into the reactor pool.

625
00:35:32,420 --> 00:35:34,500
I'll be cooked instantly.

626
00:35:35,220 --> 00:35:36,720
We shouldn't have left them alone.

627
00:35:36,870 --> 00:35:37,830
Got it.

628
00:35:38,570 --> 00:35:40,780
We couldn't stay. We were at our limits.

629
00:35:40,960 --> 00:35:43,280
That thing goes off and limits won't matter.

630
00:35:43,720 --> 00:35:45,560
Homer knows what he's doing.

631
00:35:46,760 --> 00:35:48,230
And the kid is awesome.

632
00:35:48,640 --> 00:35:49,850
Here I go.

633
00:35:52,940 --> 00:35:54,830
Can you get me closer?

634
00:35:54,910 --> 00:35:56,260
Yeah, sorry.

635
00:35:57,980 --> 00:36:02,000
I thought everybody your age was a whiz with a remote.

636
00:36:02,100 --> 00:36:03,200
Not me.

637
00:36:03,310 --> 00:36:05,650
Lower me a little more.

638
00:36:07,920 --> 00:36:10,110
Can you get me a little closer?

639
00:36:15,160 --> 00:36:16,080
Okay.

640
00:36:16,380 --> 00:36:19,570
Now hit the switch that says claw release.

641
00:36:29,390 --> 00:36:30,580
One down.

642
00:36:33,400 --> 00:36:35,110
Once this is fixed,

643
00:36:36,360 --> 00:36:38,130
shoot me and get out.

644
00:36:38,840 --> 00:36:41,040
I don't want to become one of them.

645
00:37:02,900 --> 00:37:05,230
If I haven't said anything lately,

646
00:37:05,990 --> 00:37:10,380
thank you so much,universe.

647
00:37:10,660 --> 00:37:13,220
For the Zombie Apocalypse!

648
00:37:16,280 --> 00:37:20,560
And for Doctor Merch and my whole situation!

649
00:37:21,160 --> 00:37:24,110
And for, well I don't know, let's see, what else.

650
00:37:24,110 --> 00:37:26,820
The Badlands Nuclear Power Plant!

651
00:37:27,080 --> 00:37:28,190
And yes!

652
00:37:28,190 --> 00:37:30,550
Points to you, universe!

653
00:37:30,550 --> 00:37:33,200
Points to you for dragging my ass

654
00:37:33,200 --> 00:37:36,290
all the way to South Dakota to die!

655
00:37:40,510 --> 00:37:42,920
That was sarcasm.

656
00:37:49,910 --> 00:37:52,110
I am not like other boys.

657
00:37:52,130 --> 00:37:54,020
I do not give mercy.

658
00:37:55,450 --> 00:37:56,550
Go home!

659
00:38:00,080 --> 00:38:01,960
I don't have anything for you!

660
00:38:03,070 --> 00:38:05,680
Can't you find somebody to munch on?

661
00:38:09,930 --> 00:38:10,970
Oh God,

662
00:38:12,700 --> 00:38:14,740
really is puppies and kittens.

663
00:38:23,150 --> 00:38:27,040
Two...more...inches.

664
00:38:31,720 --> 00:38:33,960
Now hit the claw release again.

665
00:38:40,090 --> 00:38:42,520
Almost... there.

666
00:38:48,950 --> 00:38:50,300
Homer, it worked.

667
00:38:50,790 --> 00:38:52,060
How about that?

668
00:38:52,560 --> 00:38:53,790
We did good.

669
00:38:54,090 --> 00:38:55,750
All right, now let me get you out of there.

670
00:38:56,210 --> 00:38:57,720
Shoot me now.

671
00:39:01,430 --> 00:39:03,840
I already killed my father. I don't want to kill you.

672
00:39:05,060 --> 00:39:06,830
You don't make it easy.

673
00:39:07,360 --> 00:39:09,420
No, no, no! No, no, no! No!

674
00:39:11,220 --> 00:39:12,190
No!

675
00:39:34,890 --> 00:39:36,070
Here he comes.

676
00:39:43,630 --> 00:39:46,130
Hey, kid! Wait! Wait up!

677
00:39:46,600 --> 00:39:48,000
Homer saved us!

678
00:39:48,000 --> 00:39:49,830
That's right. He saved the whole town!

679
00:39:49,830 --> 00:39:50,940
It's not that!

680
00:39:52,760 --> 00:39:54,010
I couldn't save him.

681
00:39:55,030 --> 00:39:56,890
I know, I know. We heard.

682
00:40:00,690 --> 00:40:02,180
You did everything you could.

683
00:40:02,410 --> 00:40:03,730
You gave him mercy.

684
00:40:07,890 --> 00:40:10,380
You remind me of my ex-wife, back from Costco.

685
00:40:10,590 --> 00:40:11,880
Who'd marry you?

686
00:40:13,240 --> 00:40:15,550
Several women, I'll have you know.

687
00:40:15,770 --> 00:40:17,670
None with very good taste

688
00:40:18,250 --> 00:40:19,870
or staying power.

689
00:40:19,920 --> 00:40:21,140
So it all worked.

690
00:40:21,430 --> 00:40:22,560
We're safe.

691
00:40:23,140 --> 00:40:24,290
From the meltdown.

692
00:40:24,910 --> 00:40:26,050
Nothing else.

693
00:40:29,600 --> 00:40:31,210
Is this a battery charger?

694
00:40:32,150 --> 00:40:34,480
Yeah. I couldn't find a truck that I could fix,

695
00:40:34,480 --> 00:40:36,010
so that'll keep us going.

696
00:40:36,230 --> 00:40:38,120
All right, so we can get back on the trail.

697
00:40:38,120 --> 00:40:39,210
But where to?

698
00:40:39,280 --> 00:40:42,030
Given the fact that we've lost Patient Zero.

699
00:40:45,510 --> 00:40:46,770
Great news!

700
00:40:47,090 --> 00:40:49,270
The vodka made perfect fuel

701
00:40:49,600 --> 00:40:51,020
for ten minutes!

702
00:40:51,130 --> 00:40:52,270
What happened?

703
00:40:52,380 --> 00:40:53,580
Crash landing

704
00:40:53,990 --> 00:40:55,640
about a hundred miles out of town.

705
00:40:55,640 --> 00:40:57,270
Wow, you covered a lot of ground.

706
00:40:57,270 --> 00:40:58,080
Did you hitchhike?

707
00:40:58,080 --> 00:40:59,400
Ten miles, whatever.

708
00:40:59,480 --> 00:41:01,500
It felt like a hundred miles when you're walking.

709
00:41:03,620 --> 00:41:05,520
So what happened to Amelia?

710
00:41:10,060 --> 00:41:11,200
Oh no.

711
00:41:11,370 --> 00:41:12,980
You didn't give her mercy?

712
00:41:13,080 --> 00:41:14,640
It didn't feel right, somehow.

713
00:41:14,720 --> 00:41:17,070
So you just let her follow you?

714
00:41:18,060 --> 00:41:21,580
That... felt... right, somehow.

715
00:41:23,490 --> 00:41:25,170
Okay, what do you want us to do?

716
00:41:25,420 --> 00:41:27,420
No, no! No, no, no, no, no! No!

717
00:41:28,030 --> 00:41:28,810
No!

718
00:41:30,260 --> 00:41:32,020
She is not hurting us!

719
00:41:34,080 --> 00:41:35,120
I don't know.

720
00:41:36,150 --> 00:41:38,350
Maybe it's time for a different kind of mercy.

721
00:41:48,390 --> 00:41:49,240
Okay.

722
00:41:50,770 --> 00:41:51,820
Climb aboard.

